Title: PERFORMANCE EVALUATIONS OF THE ATLAS ENDCAP AND FORWARD LIQUID ARGON CALORIMETERS  
Author: PETER LOCH PIERRE SAVARD 
Address: Tucson, AZ 85721, USA  Montreal, QUEBEC H3C 3J7, Canada  
Affiliation: Experimental Elementary Particle Physics Department of Physics University of Arizona  Groupe de Physique des Particules Laboratoire de Physique Nucleaire University de Montreal  
Abstract: The performance of the ATLAS EndCap (EC) and Forward (FCal) liquid argon calorimeters for hadrons and jets has been evaluated using a detailed GEANT detector simulation and the GCALOR hadronic shower model. The results indicate a fairly linear response of the FCal to high energetic pions (100 900 GeV) and jets (500 GeV to 5 TeV) and sufficient energy resolution. First studies of W mass spectroscopy and jet tagging in the presence of pile up from minimum bias events at LHC, show promising physics performance for the compact integrated design of the EC and FCal in ATLAS.
